import{_ as e,o as r,c as a,a7 as o}from"./chunks/framework.C5fSpjcB.js";const g=JSON.parse('{"title":"Worldbuilding","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"en/story/worldbuilding.md","filePath":"en/story/worldbuilding.md","lastUpdated":1775394001000}'),n={name:"en/story/worldbuilding.md"};function d(i,t,s,h,l,c){return r(),a("div",null,[...t[0]||(t[0]=[o('<h1 id="worldbuilding" tabindex="-1">Worldbuilding <a class="header-anchor" href="#worldbuilding" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Worldbuilding&quot;">​</a></h1><p>Morimens is set in a world deeply influenced by the <strong>Cthulhu Mythos</strong> and Lovecraftian horror. This page catalogues the key concepts, factions, and lore elements of the game&#39;s world.</p><h2 id="cthulhu-mythos-concepts" tabindex="-1">Cthulhu Mythos Concepts <a class="header-anchor" href="#cthulhu-mythos-concepts" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Cthulhu Mythos Concepts&quot;">​</a></h2><p>The game draws from and reinterprets classic Lovecraftian concepts:</p><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Game Concept</th><th>Mythos Inspiration</th><th>Role in Morimens</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Awakeners (唤醒体)</td><td>Awakened humans</td><td>Playable characters with eldritch powers</td></tr><tr><td>Designated Realms</td><td>Domains of cosmic entities</td><td>Four schools of power (Chaos, Aequor, Caro, Ultra)</td></tr><tr><td>Madness Points (狂气)</td><td>Sanity loss</td><td>Combat mechanic; triggers Madness Burst at 100</td></tr><tr><td>Silver Key</td><td>The Silver Key (Lovecraft)</td><td>Combat energy; activates Key Orders at 1000</td></tr><tr><td>The Keeper</td><td>Investigator / Curator</td><td>Player character; protector of Awakeners</td></tr><tr><td>Night of Oblivion (忘却前夜)</td><td>Cosmic apocalypse</td><td>The world-ending event the story revolves around</td></tr><tr><td>Investigation</td><td>Mythos investigation</td><td>Roguelite exploration mode</td></tr><tr><td>Tentacles (Aequor)</td><td>Deep Ones / Cthulhu</td><td>Summoned entities in combat</td></tr><tr><td>Embryos (Caro)</td><td>Shoggoths / flesh horror</td><td>Created and consumed cards</td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id="the-world" tabindex="-1">The World <a class="header-anchor" href="#the-world" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;The World&quot;">​</a></h2><blockquote><p>This world is dying. Facing a hidden and unspeakable calamity, Mythag University -- one of the few who know the truth -- has resolved to awaken a power that shares its origin with the disaster itself, forging bonds with human weapons who walk the edge of madness, to resist this vast crisis.</p></blockquote><p>The world of Morimens is steeped in a <strong>Victorian/Edwardian fog-London aesthetic</strong>, blended with Lovecraftian cosmic horror. The core theme is <strong>Memory and Forgetting</strong> -- the tension between what we choose to remember and what the world forces us to lose.</p><blockquote><p>&quot;You are no savior -- merely someone walking the edge of madness, stepping closer to the truth, one step at a time.&quot;</p></blockquote><h3 id="the-night-of-oblivion" tabindex="-1">The Night of Oblivion <a class="header-anchor" href="#the-night-of-oblivion" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;The Night of Oblivion&quot;">​</a></h3><p>The &quot;Night of Oblivion&quot; (忘却前夜) is the central catastrophe of Morimens&#39; world. It is a cyclical event that threatens to erase memory, identity, and ultimately existence itself. The Keeper and the Awakeners stand against this tide.</p><h3 id="the-erosion" tabindex="-1">The Erosion <a class="header-anchor" href="#the-erosion" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;The Erosion&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Hundreds of years ago, the <strong>Erosion</strong> (融蚀) silently descended upon the world. Life, sanity, memory -- everything that humanity imbues with &quot;meaning&quot; is gradually erased by the Erosion, leaving no trace. People remain utterly unaware of its existence. Those infected by the Erosion mutate into monsters and are completely erased from the world -- including all memories others have of them.</p><blockquote><p>&quot;Welcome to Mythag University, Keeper. But there is nothing to congratulate -- you will be unknown, unrewarded, unremembered.&quot;</p></blockquote><h3 id="key-roles" tabindex="-1">Key Roles <a class="header-anchor" href="#key-roles" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Key Roles&quot;">​</a></h3><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Title</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>The Keeper</strong> (守密人)</td><td>Secret Keeper</td><td>A student/agent of Mythag University. Investigates the cause of lost memories, leading Awakeners into battle and assembling strategic card decks to uncover a twisted, maddening truth</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Awakened Ones</strong> (唤醒体)</td><td>Awakeners</td><td>Human weapons walking the edge of madness, carriers of a power that shares its origin with the Erosion. Each Awakener has a unique personality, backstory, and personal story questline</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="factions" tabindex="-1">Factions <a class="header-anchor" href="#factions" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Factions&quot;">​</a></h3><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Faction</th><th>Base</th><th>Role</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Mythag University</strong> (弥萨格大学)</td><td>Kingdom of Leo</td><td>Player&#39;s home faction; one of the few organizations aware of the Erosion&#39;s true nature</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Sculptors&#39; Association</strong> (雕塑家协会)</td><td>Secret</td><td>A clandestine organization operating in the shadows</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Church of the Lightbearers</strong> (持光者教会)</td><td>Hidden -- wherever Erosion occurs</td><td>A religious group active in areas affected by Erosion</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Seafarers</strong> (航海者)</td><td>Oceans / coastal regions</td><td>Maritime power seeking to restore the sunken kingdom of Lemuria</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Aramites</strong> (亚兰人)</td><td>Lemwash Desert (vanished)</td><td>A desert people hidden within violent storms; now disappeared</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mystia Treaty Committee</strong> (密斯提亚条约委员会)</td><td>Offices worldwide</td><td>A transnational organization with branches in every nation</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cult Organizations</strong> (邪教组织)</td><td>Various</td><td>Hostile forces encountered throughout the story</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Erosion Entities</strong> (融蚀体)</td><td>N/A</td><td>Mutated beings created by the Erosion phenomenon, including humanoid and cooperative types</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="key-locations" tabindex="-1">Key Locations <a class="header-anchor" href="#key-locations" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Key Locations&quot;">​</a></h3><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Location</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Londinium</strong> (伦蒂尼恩)</td><td>Major City</td><td>A Victorian-style metropolis and the game&#39;s core stage, divided into multiple districts</td></tr><tr><td><strong>East District</strong> (东区)</td><td>City District</td><td>The impoverished district of Londinium; setting of Chapter 1 &quot;East District Secrets&quot;</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mythag University</strong> (弥萨格大学)</td><td>Institution</td><td>Located in the Kingdom of Leo; the player&#39;s main base of operations</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Kingdom of Leo</strong> (狮子王国)</td><td>Nation</td><td>Home country of Mythag University&#39;s main campus</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Rainy Town</strong> (雨镇)</td><td>Town</td><td>Setting of the side story &quot;Shadows of Rainy Town&quot;</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Elworth</strong> (艾尔沃斯)</td><td>Otherworldly Location</td><td>A living place that rearranges itself; &quot;calls&quot; to Lily and Helot</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Black Pool of Mythag</strong> (弥萨格黑潭)</td><td>Otherworldly Location</td><td>Guarded by Lotan; connected to Tawil&#39;s awakening</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Aequor</strong> (深渊海域)</td><td>Otherworldly Ocean</td><td>An oceanic domain connected to the deep-sea realm</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Lemuria</strong> (雷姆利亚)</td><td>Lost Kingdom</td><td>An ancient sunken kingdom the Seafarers seek to restore</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Sanatorium</strong> (疗养院)</td><td>Location</td><td>Setting of Chapter 4; harbors dark secrets</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Lightless Realm</strong> (无光秘境)</td><td>Dungeon</td><td>Challenge dungeon for unlocking character star upgrades</td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id="the-four-realms-as-cosmic-domains" tabindex="-1">The Four Realms as Cosmic Domains <a class="header-anchor" href="#the-four-realms-as-cosmic-domains" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;The Four Realms as Cosmic Domains&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Each Designated Realm represents a different facet of the unknowable:</p><ul><li><span class="realm-badge realm-chaos">Chaos</span> -- The primordial void from which all things emerged. Represents formlessness and infinite potential.</li><li><span class="realm-badge realm-aequor">Aequor</span> -- The abyssal deep, where ancient entities slumber beneath impossible pressures.</li><li><span class="realm-badge realm-caro">Caro</span> -- The flesh that reshapes itself, evoking body horror and mutation beyond natural law.</li><li><span class="realm-badge realm-ultra">Ultra</span> -- The dimensions beyond human perception, where time and space lose meaning.</li></ul><h2 id="mythology-references" tabindex="-1">Mythology References <a class="header-anchor" href="#mythology-references" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Mythology References&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Many characters in Morimens draw inspiration from the Cthulhu Mythos:</p><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Character</th><th>Mythological Archetype</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Tulu (图鲁)</td><td>Cthulhu</td><td>Aequor SSR; titled &quot;Young Lord / Slumbering Lord&quot;</td></tr><tr><td>Rhea (雷娅)</td><td>Shub-Niggurath (Black Goat)</td><td>Caro SSR; nicknamed &quot;Goat Mom&quot; by the community</td></tr><tr><td>Uuhashi (尤乌哈希)</td><td>Yog-Sothoth</td><td>Caro SSR; name phonetically similar</td></tr><tr><td>Lotan (萝坦)</td><td>Leviathan / Lotan</td><td>Starter SR/SSR; guardian of the Black Pool of Mythag</td></tr><tr><td>Alva (艾尔瓦)</td><td>Nyarlathotep</td><td>Chaos Tier 0; possibly inspired by the Outer God&#39;s messenger</td></tr><tr><td>24</td><td>Unknown / Original</td><td>Limited Tier 0; a mysterious figure known only by a number</td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id="collaborations" tabindex="-1">Collaborations <a class="header-anchor" href="#collaborations" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Collaborations&quot;">​</a></h2><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Collaboration</th><th>Partner</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Saya no Uta</td><td>Saya no Uta (沙耶之歌)</td><td>A crossover event with the classic visual novel, introducing collaboration characters</td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id="timeline" tabindex="-1">Timeline <a class="header-anchor" href="#timeline" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Timeline&quot;">​</a></h2><p>The main story spans approximately <strong>800,000 characters of text</strong>, told in an episodic unit-drama format across two major arcs:</p><h3 id="oblivion-chapter-忘却篇" tabindex="-1">Oblivion Chapter (忘却篇) <a class="header-anchor" href="#oblivion-chapter-忘却篇" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Oblivion Chapter (忘却篇)&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Prologue through Chapter 7. The Keeper arrives at Londinium, bonds with the initial four Awakeners (Doll, Ramona, Lotan, Ogier), and uncovers the truth behind the Erosion.</p><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Chapter</th><th>Title</th><th>Summary</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Prologue</td><td>Prologue</td><td>The Keeper arrives at Londinium and begins their journey at Mythag University. Bonds with the starting four Awakeners and learns about the Erosion and the nature of Awakened Ones</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>East District Secrets</td><td>A layered investigation in the impoverished East District: from a workshop manager, to a suspicious doctor, to a cult. The truth centers on a girl controlled by dark forces who sacrifices herself to protect those she loves</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>Metamorphosis</td><td>The bonds between Keeper and Awakeners deepen. The Keeper witnesses the cruelty of Erosion-induced metamorphosis firsthand and begins to understand that Awakeners are not merely weapons</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>Chapter 3</td><td>Multiple factions vie for power. The Sculptors&#39; Association, Church of the Lightbearers, and others emerge, while Mythag University&#39;s true motives come under question</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>Chapter 4</td><td>A major turning point. The Keeper brings rescued girl Lily to the Sanatorium, only to discover a greater crisis lurking within its walls</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>Chapter 5</td><td>Multiple plot threads converge. Foreshadowing from earlier chapters pays off as faction plans collide</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>Chapter 6</td><td>Factions show their true colors. The Keeper questions the cost of &quot;protecting the truth.&quot; The hidden connection between Mythag University and the Erosion surfaces</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>Chapter 7</td><td>The Oblivion Chapter finale. Includes boss stages like 7-18 &quot;Kindling.&quot; The Keeper faces the ultimate test: forget the pain and find peace, or remember everything and carry the burden forward</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="stellar-chapter-星辰篇" tabindex="-1">Stellar Chapter (星辰篇) <a class="header-anchor" href="#stellar-chapter-星辰篇" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Stellar Chapter (星辰篇)&quot;">​</a></h3><p>A new arc following the Oblivion Chapter&#39;s conclusion. New cosmic forces emerge and the meaning of &quot;awakening&quot; deepens.</p><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>Chapter</th><th>Title</th><th>Stages</th><th>Summary</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Prologue</td><td>Stellar Prologue</td><td>--</td><td>The world&#39;s landscape has shifted. New threats and allies appear simultaneously</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>Chapter 1</td><td>1-1 to 1-14</td><td>Awakeners change under the influence of stellar power. The Keeper must re-understand their companions&#39; true nature</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>Metamorphosis</td><td>2-1 to 2-18</td><td>Echoing the Oblivion Chapter&#39;s arc of the same name, but with deeper meaning -- stellar power brings inner awakening, not just outer change</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>Chapter 3</td><td>3-1 to 3-11</td><td>Hidden truths within prophecies gradually surface. The guidance of the stars conceals a grander plan</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>Paradise</td><td>4-0 to 4-16</td><td>The chapter with the steepest difficulty curve. <em>&quot;Why has the Black Sun eclipsed the sky?&quot;</em> The Black Sun imagery pervades the entire chapter, culminating in an extremely challenging final boss</td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id="see-also" tabindex="-1">See Also <a class="header-anchor" href="#see-also" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;See Also&quot;">​</a></h2><ul><li><a href="./">Story &amp; Lore Overview</a></li><li><a href="./main.html">Main Story</a></li><li><a href="./../realms/">Realms Overview</a></li></ul>',38)])])}const m=e(n,[["render",d]]);export{g as __pageData,m as default};
